[00:01.760] Illusions of pastoral peace. | 田园和平的幻想。
[00:06.666] The quiet life of the country has never appealed to me. | 乡村的宁静生活从未吸引过我。
[00:09.916] City-born and city-bred, I have always regarded the country as something you look at through a train window, | 生于城市、长于城市，我一直把乡村看作是透过火车窗户才能看到的东西，
[00:16.486] or something you occasionally visit during the weekend. | 或是周末偶尔去拜访的地方。
